<HEADLINE>
FT  26 JUL 93 / Thousands of commuters to face disruption
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TIM KING
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Thousands of London commuters face disruption of railway services to and
from Charing Cross station today, Tim King writes.
British Rail will not run any trains to Waterloo East or Charing Cross for
the next three weeks. The stations have been closed because work at London
Bridge (above) has cut off the entry route. Main line services from Ashford,
Kent and suburban line services from Dartford via Bexleyheath are being
diverted to Victoria and the frequency of trains will be reduced. All other
services are being diverted to Cannon Street. Tickets issued by British Rail
for travel to Charing Cross will be valid on the Underground between Cannon
Street and Victoria stations. The Underground station at Cannon Street will
be open longer hours and at the weekend. British Rail is paying London
Transport to provide extra buses from Cannon Street.
