<HEADLINE>
FT  26 JUL 93 / Spanish Finance Minister warns that recession shows no signs
of ending
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Spain's new finance minister, Pedro Solbes, has warned that the country's
recession shows no sign of ending and that a sharp reduction of labour costs
is required to stimulate the troubled economy. He indicated that there was
little chance over the next two years of reducing Spain's budget deficit and
said he would amend a package of ambitious targets set by the government for
economic and monetary union convergence. Page 20
Bundesbank will not follow Fed's lead Page 4
Economic Viewpoint, Page 21
Currencies Page 33
