<HEADLINE>
FT  24 JUL 93 / Books: Lippi
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICIA MORISON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The missing name in your library of great Italian masters of the
quattrocento may well be Fra Filippo Lippi, writes Patricia Morison. Few
books have been devoted to this marvellously distinctive and beautiful
Florentine painter, and none in English. Jeffrey Ruda's Fra Filippo Lippi:
Life and Work with a Complete Catalogue (Phaidon Pounds 95, 560 pages) fills
the gap admirably, if expensively, with clear and unpretentious text and
many beautiful illustrations such as that pictured above: 'The Madonna and
child with the Birth of the Virgin and the Meeting of Joachim and Anna.'
