</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Savers withdrew more money from building societies than they deposited in
June, creating a net outflow of Pounds 56m. This followed a net inflow of
Pounds 700m in May and more than Pounds 1bn in April. The net inflow for the
second quarter as a whole was Pounds 1.7bn, compared to Pounds 77m in the
same period last year. The Building Societies Association blamed June's
outflow on seasonal factors combined with the BT3 share offer, for which
many savers withdrew money.
