<HEADLINE>
FT  24 JUL 93 / International Company News: Approval for demerger at
Marriott
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MARRIOTT Corporation, the lodging and food services group, won shareholder
approval at yesterday's annual meeting for its controversial proposal to
split the company into two.
It wants to demerge its main operating interests - the lodging business and
food services operations, to be known as Marriott International - from its
property assets and the bulk of the group's debts, which will be grouped in
a business to be known as Host Marriott.
Just before yesterday's meeting Marriott also announced it had reached a
settlement with a group which had opposed the plan: preferred shareholders
who argued the split would hurt them financially.
The settlement involves the dissidents converting their preferred stock into
common stock before the demerger goes ahead, and a payment to them which the
company described as 'immaterial'.
The company has already seen off a bondholder revolt by agreeing to swap
Dollars 1.525bn of existing bonds for new high- yielding debt.
</TEXT>
