FT  24 JUL 93 / International Company News: CSM challenges bourse
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RONALD VAN DE KROL
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   AMSTERDAM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CSM, the Dutch food group, has opened legal proceedings against the
Amsterdam stock exchange in a dispute over the number of anti-takeover
measures listed Dutch companies can use, writes Ronald van de Krol in
Amsterdam.
CSM is challenging the bourse's decision to terminate its listing in June
1994 if it does not comply with new rules requiring companies to limit their
anti-takeover mechanisms to two.
At issue is CSM's use of non-convertible depositary receipts, a type of
share which the Amsterdam bourse wants to discourage.
