held at 2.73p making a 4.25p (4.18p) total. Earnings per share fell to 0.1p
(2.6p).
With 'evidence emerging of a recovery in the property market' the group has
exchanged contracts to acquire a 'large' town centre commercial estate in
Liverpool for Pounds 5m in conjunction with Haigside and Western Securities.
Southend will have a 50 per cent equity interest in the joint venture.
