<DATELINE>
   ONE IN THREE women have experienced sexual harassment at work
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
but only 14 per cent of those who have suffered have told their managers,
according to a survey for the BBC, conducted by MORI, the market research
group, Diane Summers writes.
The survey of 700 women found that less than half (49 per cent) of those
experiencing harassment had discussed it with others. Jokes and lewd
