<HEADLINE>
FT  24 JUL 93 / Romania fails to agree IMF deal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By VIRGINIA MARSH
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   Bucharest
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Romania has failed to reach agreement with the International Monetary Fund
for a new standby arrangement which would unlock Dollars 3bn of foreign
loans, Virginia Marsh in Bucharest.
An IMF mission left Bucharest yesterday after two weeks of negotiations
failed to produce an agreement to replace the previous one which expired
last March. Mr Maxwell Watson, head of the mission, said the outstanding
issues were the need to restructure state-owned enterprises and to curb
inflation.
The country's failure to impose stricter financial discipline on state
companies, which have built up Dollars 2.4bn in inter-enterprise debt, is
seen as a major contribution to inflation. Inflation reached 225 per cent a
year in May.
